{"key":"processedPost-8042912","value":{"id":8042912,"first":8024543,"last":8043362,"when":1203453917,"utime":"02/19/08 10:45 PM","content":"You need to make sure the jars are totally out of the water when you steam them.  Otherwise, the water splashes up over the tops of the jars as it boils, getting your verm barrier damp.<br /><br />If the trich is showing just below the verm barrier or on it, then that's the cause.  If it's showing up at the points of inoculation, then you introduced it at that time either through poor sterile technique or contaminated syringe.<br />RR","title":"Re: trich on 80% colonized jars","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}